libibvpp
------------------------------------------
Libibvpp is a C++ wrapper around libibverbs, which is part of the OpenFabrics
software suite (www.openfabrics.org). For the most part, Libibvpp provides a
minimalistic C++ wrapper interface to libibverbs, while providing complete
resource management through the use of C++ TR1 smart pointers: specifically,
the tr1::shared_ptr and tr1::weak_ptr classes.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.5-1
  libgcc1-13.4.0-1
  libibverbs1-1.2.1-1bl2
  libibvpp-devel-0.1-1bl2
  libibvpp0-0.1-1bl2
  libstdc++6-13.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  autoconf-15-2
  automake-20250528-1
  binutils-2.45.1-1
  cygport-0.37.3-1
  gcc-core-13.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-13.4.0-1
  libibverbs-devel-1.2.1-1bl2
  libtool-2.5.4-1
  make-4.4.1-2

Canonical website:
  https://web.archive.org/web/20211023042735/http://ti.arc.nasa.gov/opensource/projects/libibvpp/

Canonical download:
  https://web.archive.org/web/20211023042735/http://ti.arc.nasa.gov/m/opensource/downloads/libibvpp-0.1.tar.gz#/libibvpp-0.1.tar

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack libibvpp-0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./libibvpp-0.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/libibvpp-0.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libibvpp-0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libibvpp0-0.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libibvpp-devel-0.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(libibvpp)
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_asyncwatch.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_device_list.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_devinfo.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_rc_pingpong.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_srq_pingpong.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_uc_pingpong.exe
  /usr/bin/ibvpp_ud_pingpong.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/libibvpp.README
  /usr/share/doc/libibvpp/AUTHORS
  /usr/share/doc/libibvpp/COPYING
  /usr/share/doc/libibvpp/README

(libibvpp0)
  /usr/bin/cygibvpp-0.dll

(libibvpp-devel)
  /usr/include/ibvpp.h
  /usr/include/ibvpp_utility.h
  /usr/lib/libibvpp.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/libibvpp.pc

